cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it proposes a novel recurrent neural network model for extracting information from images and videos. Additionally, the paper evaluates the model on several image classification tasks, which further supports its categorization under cs.CV.

The paper also involves the use of reinforcement learning methods to train the model, which suggests that it could also be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).

Furthermore, the model's ability to control the amount of computation independently of the input image size could make it relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.

Finally, the paper's evaluation of the model on a dynamic visual control problem could make it relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) category.
